text.tspan: Number of people living in extreme poverty by region, 1820 to
This data is calculated based on a ‘cost of basic needs’ approach. It represents the number of people unable to meet basic needs
(including minimal nutrition and adequately heated shelter) according to prices of locally-available goods and services at the time.
